{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13541/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13541"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:35:41"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed, zoom"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Man and woman look at each other, guests watch around them"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13541","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13541"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/6c779d95-3add-45c8-b2e4-80c263166a9a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:33:59.008Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Tellingly, the witnesses at their wedding come entirely from Reynolds’s business. Cyril is an exception—of sorts—but Reynolds has no personal life to speak of; his business is deeply intwined with what happens outside of it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:31.94805194805202,129.35064935064932,296.1038961038961,149.61038961038966"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/43bd83ca-5144-408c-9e45-8d9af8600fdb","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:34:16.324Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cyril is standing between Alma and Reynolds but behind them, with the other guests, not interrupting their sight of one another. While she had once been Alma’s competitor in many ways, both vying for the position of primary woman in Reynolds’s life, she has accepted the change and now looks on with fondness.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:687.2727272727273,300,264.1558441558442,755.0649350649351"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1/6425db62-4e1b-4f3a-9d80-bdbd33fd81ee","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:34:38.741Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma appears to be wearing baby’s breath in her hair, a flower commonly associated with purity, love, and rebirth. She has brought life back into the dead House of Woodcock and into Reynolds’s life as a whole. Cyril and Reynolds both wear it as a boutonniere, matching her and symbolizing how they have been won over by her, and are now all joined by the bonds of family. Interestingly, the flower is also toxic to humans and can cause reactions if ingested or if physical contact is made with it. This is a nod to her poisoning of Reynolds, which is what led to this marriage itself. Although she carries poison with her, it is ultimately in service of love and beauty.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13541/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:399.7402597402598,120,1006.7532467532469,648.3116883116883"}}}]}]}]}